ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.209                Enzyme
NAME        3(or 17)alpha-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase;
            3(17)alpha-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     3(or 17)alpha-hydroxysteroid:NAD(P)+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    androsterone + NAD(P)+ = 5alpha-androstane-3,17-dione + NAD(P)H + H+ [RN:R02476 R02477]
ALL_REAC    R02476 R02477
SUBSTRATE   androsterone [CPD:C00523];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     5alpha-androstane-3,17-dione [CPD:C00674];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     Acts on the 3alpha-hydroxy group of androgens of the 5alpha-androstane series; and also, more slowly, on the 17alpha-hydroxy group of both androgenic and estrogenic substrates (cf. EC 1.1.1.51 3(or 17)beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase).
